# MOSC Redesign Hub Card: Rounded Corners + Containment

## Overview

Hub section cards on `/mosc-redesign/*` (Catholicate, Holy Synod, Saints, The Church, Directory, etc.) use a shared **`MoscHubCardMedia`** component. The requirement is:

1. **`rounded-xl` on all four corners** of the visible photo (not just top-left/top-right).
2. **Full image visible** ‚Äî no head crop on portraits.
3. **No empty letterbox gap** at the bottom of the image frame.

**Canonical implementation:** [`src/app/mosc-redesign/(syro)/components/MoscHubCardMedia.tsx`](mdc:src/app/mosc-redesign/(syro)/components/MoscHubCardMedia.tsx)  
**Shell CSS:** [`src/styles/mosc-redesign-shell.css`](mdc:src/styles/mosc-redesign-shell.css) (`.mosc-hub-card-media*`, `.mosc-hub-card-media--intrinsic`)

---

## Problem: Why Naive Fixes Fail

| Approach | Rounded corners | Full image | Bottom gap |
|----------|-----------------|------------|------------|
| Fixed landscape box + `object-cover` | ‚úÖ All four | ‚ùå Crops heads | ‚úÖ None |
| Fixed aspect box + `fill` + `object-contain` | ‚ùå Only top two on visible photo | ‚úÖ Full image | ‚ùå White strip below image |
| Intrinsic height + `w-full h-auto` + clip | ‚úÖ All four | ‚úÖ Full image | ‚úÖ None |

**Root cause of ‚Äúsquare bottom corners‚Äù:** With `object-contain` inside a **taller fixed aspect box**, the photo is a smaller rectangle pinned to the top. The container is rounded, but the **visible image** ends with square bottom edges above empty space.

**Root cause of bottom padding/gap:** Fixed `aspect-[2/3]` (or any ratio that does not match the asset) + `fill` forces extra height the image never fills.

---

## Solution: Two Frame Modes

### 1. Portrait (default) ‚Äî intrinsic height

Use when the card shows **portraits, icons, or mixed hub photos** (Catholicate, Saints, Holy Synod, The Church, etc.).

- **Container:** `max-w-[220px]`, `rounded-xl`, `overflow-hidden`, **`height: auto`** (class `mosc-hub-card-media--intrinsic`).
- **Image:** Next.js `Image` with **`width` / `height`** (layout hint), **`w-full h-auto`** ‚Äî **not** `fill`.
- **Clip:** Parent `overflow: hidden` + `border-radius: 0.75rem` on container, wrapper `span`, and `img`.
- **Result:** Frame **hugs** the image; all four corners clip correctly; no bottom letterbox.

```tsx
// ‚úÖ DO: Default portrait ‚Äî no props needed
<MoscHubCardMedia src={card.image} alt={card.alt} />

// ‚úÖ DO: Match card background when frame sits on tinted card
<MoscHubCardMedia
  src={card.image}
  alt={card.alt}
  padded={false}
  frameClassName="bg-parchment-light ring-0"
/>
```

```tsx
// ‚ùå DON'T: Fixed aspect + fill + contain for portraits
<div className="aspect-[2/3] relative">
  <Image fill className="object-contain" />
</div>
```

### 2. Landscape ‚Äî fixed tile + cover

Use **only** for wide directory-style banners (`/mosc-redesign/directory`).

- **Container:** `max-w-[280px] aspect-[280/168]`, `overflow-hidden`, `rounded-xl`.
- **Image:** `fill` + `object-cover` (+ optional `objectPosition="top"`).
- **Trade-off:** Slight crop acceptable for banner tiles; not for portrait saints/Catholicoi.

```tsx
// ‚úÖ DO: Directory banners
<MoscHubCardMedia src={imageUrl} alt={title} frame="landscape" />
```

---

## CSS Requirements (`mosc-redesign-shell.css`)

Landscape / `fill` tiles use absolute Next.js wrapper rules (`.mosc-hub-card-media > span { position: absolute; inset: 0 }`).

Portrait intrinsic mode **must override** those rules:

```css
.mosc-hub-card-media--intrinsic {
  height: auto !important;
  aspect-ratio: auto !important;
  line-height: 0;
}

.mosc-hub-card-media--intrinsic > span {
  position: relative !important;
  height: auto !important;
  overflow: hidden !important;
  border-radius: 0.75rem !important;
}

.mosc-hub-card-media--intrinsic img {
  width: 100% !important;
  height: auto !important;
  object-fit: contain !important;
  border-radius: 0.75rem !important;
}
```

**Do not remove** `.mosc-hub-card-media--intrinsic` when editing hub CSS ‚Äî portrait cards will revert to square bottom corners and bottom gaps.

---

## Component API Quick Reference

| Prop | Default | Use |
|------|---------|-----|
| `frame` | `'portrait'` | `'landscape'` only for Directory-style banners |
| `padded` | `true` | `false` when image sits flush in card (e.g. Catholicate grid) |
| `frameClassName` | ‚Äî | Match card bg: `bg-parchment-light`, `bg-white`, `ring-0` |
| `objectPosition` | `'center'` | `'top'` for landscape cover only |
| `unoptimized` | ‚Äî | Local/static assets when needed |

Placeholders use fixed `aspect-[2/3]` via `MoscHubCardMediaPlaceholder` (no image to size intrinsically).

