## Troubleshooting

### Only top corners rounded?
- Container still has fixed `aspect-*` with `fill` + `contain`. Switch to intrinsic portrait mode.

### White strip below image inside frame?
- Same as above ‚Äî frame is taller than the photo. Remove fixed aspect; use `h-auto` intrinsic sizing.

### Head cropped?
- Accidentally using `object-cover` or `frame="landscape"` on a portrait card. Use default portrait frame.

### Next.js wrapper not clipping?
- Ensure shell CSS loads (`mosc-redesign-shell.css` in syro layout).
- Verify classes: `mosc-hub-card-media`, `mosc-hub-card-media--intrinsic`, `mosc-hub-card-image--intrinsic`.

---

## Static asset paths (no hardcoded production host)

For files already under `public/`, **always use site-relative paths** ‚Äî never hardcode `https://www.mosc-temp.com/...` or `https://mosc.in/wp-content/...` for static images.

- **MOSC assets:** `/mosc/assets/images/mosc_images/...` (maps to `public/mosc/assets/images/mosc_images/`)
- **Catholicate portraits:** `/images/catholicate/...` (maps to `public/images/catholicate/`)
- **Hub cards / saints:** `/images/saints/...`, `/images/catholicate/Catholicos-N.jpg`, etc.

This keeps localhost, staging, and production working without cross-origin or Next `Image` remote-pattern dependency.

